title: SSRL BLDO Day shift report 2022-Mar-19
text: SPEAR: Beam down at start of shift due to BL-15 insertion device interlock problem. 11:00 Problem with BL-15 Insertion was repaired, Beam delivered. 500ma, top-ups every 5min. BEAM LINES: 11:00am all beamlines open except For BL-17 as staff in to work in and out of Zero hutch. 16:10 search and open BL-17. 11:00 BL4-3 Xas has shut down, turned out that Desk top (located in rack) had shut off. Once Powered back on user was able to log in and all is well. BL15-2 sample cabinet key is back in the D.O. Lock box. FAULTS: No Beamline faults. EXPERIMENTS: No problems. OTHER: Curmon was down briefly in the morning. 07:30 found kitchen outlets (PP-3) without power Reset breaker. 13:00 Rain water leaking at end of breezeway/hallway At BL10-2 area. Mop up and placed buckets. Place bucket under the usual spot just outside upstairs restrooms blg-120 near BL8-1 as well as next to BL8-1 over Vacuum chamber that is on rolling cart (moved chamber).

CATER 155842, Kly Mod 23-2: LVPS fault.
text: Kly Mod 23-2: LVPS fault. Checked the dual 24 volt outputs of both SOLAs in PLC pan: both good @ 24 VDC on DMM and supply OK lites on. Checked output fuse from supply 2, F3: good. Checked input fuse to PLC din rail 24 volt power supply: good. Green OK lite on. Cycle power several times: no good. Can't get control power on touchscreen on. Thought maybe module 7 (24 volt source) of PLC might be bad. Swapped: no good. Swapped 24 volt sink/source module 6: no good. Noticed yellow LED (D21) by fuse F8 on bottom of PLC interface board not lit like station 23-3. This LED is for status of relay K16, main control coil. Tried swapping relay K16: no good. Ran out of time. Hopefully, can get others to work on this prior to next Tuesday. Perhaps PLC Analog Input module problem? Both analog modules show green OK LED lit. See figure 1 for list of faults.

title: Kly Mod 18-3: FLK, no reset.
text: Found K13 fault count stepper stuck. Sprayed with contact cleaner and exercised counter several times. Now works smoothly. Re-energized station--on and stable.

title: 80% transmission, doing LI19 phase scans
Update on frequency counter issue
text: It seems unlikely that we'll be able to get the 5386A to work. It is a single-channel older unit, whereas the 53181A is a 2-channel newer unit and channel 2 is the one being used, so the GPIB command format might be different -- and even if it's not, the device is likely being told to read the value of channel 2, but it has no channel 2. So this avenue seems closed for now. Aaron and I looked for a spare 53181A in B122, 221, 116, 132, 118, 140, and the klystron hut. The only units we could find are the three in-service ones for linac, booster, and SPEAR RF. The current idea is to try using one of the two working units for SPEAR, since the SPEAR frequency value appears to be tied to the ALARA interlock via BTS ACM calculated efficiency. We consulted with Jeff Corbett, Steve Gierman, and Jim Sebek, and it seems as though using the booster frequency counter has the least chance of being a problem. We will first try turning off the acquisition state for the booster counter using its EDM panel, and watching for a few fills to see if there's any obvious fallout. If that seems OK, we'll bring the unit over to 117 and connect it in place of the failed unit.
